                            <comment id="17577578" author="janhoy" created="Tue, 9 Aug 2022 18:50:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I propose to target this Jira for upgrading jetty to latest 9.4 version, currently 9.4.48.v20220622. This will then be released in 9.1. The more complex and slow-moving jetty10 upgrade can then proceed for a later Solr 9.x release.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17580493" author="hossman" created="Tue, 16 Aug 2022 22:31:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is there any reason not to go ahead and commit this?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Upgrading to the latest jetty 9.4 in the main branch shouldn&apos;t make it any harder to upgrade to jetty10 later (which may or may not happen any time soon)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17580498" author="janhoy" created="Tue, 16 Aug 2022 22:51:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That was my thinking too, but then jetty10 seemed to be just around the corner. Agree this could go in anyway, and then jetty10 can happen on top of it whenever it happens.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17581798" author="jira-bot" created="Fri, 19 Aug 2022 11:38:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit e0930a7c7c4d7ac09a4ab5a7e7cf9f98455f03b0 in solr&apos;s branch refs/heads/main from Jan H&#248;ydahl&lt;br/&gt;
